local_llm_description: The image shows a black and white electronic device with a display screen that is currently turned on, displaying a waveform graph. The waveform appears to be in the form of a sine wave or a sawtooth wave, depending on the specific part of the device being viewed. This type of display can provide valuable information about electrical signals, such as voltage levels and current flows.

external_llm_result.title: Oscilloscope Screenshot with Low-Frequency Sine and Ripple
external_llm_result.summary: Rigol oscilloscope screenshot with yellow and cyan traces, where the cyan trace is higher frequency ripple and the yellow trace is lower-frequency waveform. Measurements show CH1 near 1.00 Hz and CH2 near 4.17 Hz.

structured_data.description: Rigol interface in RUN mode. Timebase shows 500 ms/div. Bottom readout shows both channels at 2.50 V/div. Frequency measurements displayed are approximately CH1 1.00 Hz and CH2 4.17 Hz.
